course: main course
---

Zest and juice the @Lemon{1}. Mince the @Shallot{1}(minced) and the @Garlic{2%clove}(minced). Strip the leaves off the @Rosemary{1%sprig}, then coarsely chop. Finely chop the @Parsley{1%bunch}(finely chopped).

Butterfly the @Chicken Breasts{2}: with your hand on top of the breasts, slice the breast carefully in half almost all the way through. Then open it up like a book and season with @Salt{pinch} and @Pepper{pinch}.

In a #bowl{}, combine half the lemon juice and half the shallots with @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon} to marinate the chicken breasts.

Meanwhile, halve the @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} and place in them in a #pot{} with enough water to cover and a large pinch of salt. Bring to a boil and cook for ~{15%minutes}, or until easily pierced with a knife. Drain.

While the potatoes cook, make the gremolata by combining parsley, half the garlic, and lemon zest in a bowl. Add @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon}, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Set aside.

Heat @Olive Oil{1/2%tablespoon} in a #non-stick pan{} over medium-high heat. Sear each chicken breast for ~{3-4%minutes} on each side, until juices run clear when pierced with a knife. Set aside and tent with #foil{} to keep warm.

Once the potatoes are drained, crush them with the side of your knife on a #cutting board{}. Heat @Olive Oil{1/2%tablespoon} in the same pan you cooked the chicken in. Add the potatoes over medium-high heat for about ~{3%minutes} per side, until golden brown. Add the rosemary and remaining garlic and cook for about ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant. Season with salt and pepper and set aside.

Toss the @Arugula{4%ounce} with @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon}, remaining shallots and lemon juice, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Serve the chicken with the gremolata on top and potatoes and arugula salad to the side.